&lt;DIV&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;&lt;STRONG&gt;6) Low/Mid Level Wizard Damage - &lt;FONT color=#ff0000&gt;Currently being discussed, This will most likely be considered as part of the class Re-Envision process.&lt;/FONT&gt;&lt;/STRONG&gt;&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;While melee have every expansion gained numerous new weapons available at the lower levels that are markedly better in dealing out damage, casters have essentially remained static, casting the same spells they have always cast since the beginning. Slightly larger mana pools and minimally better mana regen hasn't really helped this too much. This has led to a situation where they are outdamaged in both the long and short term by melee, especially Wizards because there is no pet damage to fall back on (which can be helped with newer 'trash' weapons or pet only weapons in much the same way as melee). Suggestion would be to perhaps revisit the spell lines of lower and midrange casters to give some updated spells, perhaps available off harder encounters of those levels to alleviate the situation.&lt;BR&gt;&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;&lt;STRONG&gt;7) AA Issues&lt;/STRONG&gt;&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;- Frenzied Devastation -While the last change upped the efficiency of the ability, it still seems like it loses efficiency on average at the base level. If you add in the fact that focus items aren't even considered in the equation, this ability definitely loses comparative efficiency, the better your focus items, the worse off you are. It would actually be nice if this actually gained slightly in efficiency as you got more levels simply because it currently on par with similar melee abilities to gain DPS which don't seem to have the same problems. &lt;FONT color=#ff0000&gt;&lt;STRONG&gt;Currently being discussed&lt;/STRONG&gt;&lt;/FONT&gt;&lt;BR&gt;- Ward of Destruction - The damage done by the spell even at the max level is extremely low and the static nature of it also makes the damage output even less reliable.&amp;nbsp; &lt;STRONG&gt;&lt;FONT color=#ff0000&gt;Currently being evaluated.&amp;nbsp; Rashere is currently looking into ways to make this AA more useful. &lt;BR&gt;&lt;/FONT&gt;&lt;/STRONG&gt;- Familiars - Should be more of a reason to use the GoD familiars, currently they are only used on short fights where you don't have a Bard because of the lack of mana regen and resists as well as the fact they are only dedicated to one resist type. It would also be nice if the other AA familiars were changed to the same 1 minute recast and instant cast as these. - &lt;FONT color=#ff0000&gt;&lt;STRONG&gt;Currently being discussed&lt;/STRONG&gt; &lt;/FONT&gt;&lt;BR&gt;- Strong Root – Shorten recast timer and make it so Greater Fetter doesn’t overwrite it. - &lt;STRONG&gt;&lt;FONT color=#ff0000&gt;Currently being discussed&lt;/FONT&gt;&lt;/STRONG&gt;&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;&lt;STRONG&gt;8) Stuns -&lt;/STRONG&gt; &lt;STRONG&gt;&lt;FONT color=#ff0000&gt;NEW&lt;/FONT&gt;&lt;/STRONG&gt;&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;Stuns currently seems to be less than they should be, at least compared to how they used to work. One of the current problems is that they cap to low to be as useful as they could be, and a side effect of the cap is that it leaves a gap in being able to use stuns while you are leveling up at some points. Would be nice to see the level cap raised so that you can at least attempt to stun yellow mobs when you are at the max level. Raising the current cap on the higher level stuns by 2-3 levels would make them more useful in groups as well as fix the gap problem.&lt;BR&gt;&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
