      <title>Re: Class issues lists – Updated Version (Wizard)</title>
      <link>http://eqforums.station.sony.com/eq/board/message?board.id=wizardbalance&amp;message.id=3031#M3031</link>
      <description>&lt;DIV&gt;&lt;FONT color=#ff00ff&gt;&lt;STRONG&gt;Wizard&lt;/STRONG&gt; - &lt;FONT size=2&gt;&lt;STRONG&gt;List Update scheduled for&amp;nbsp;05/06/05&lt;/STRONG&gt;&lt;/FONT&gt;&lt;/FONT&gt;&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;1) &lt;STRONG&gt;Short to Medium term damage -&lt;/STRONG&gt; &lt;FONT color=#ff0000&gt;&lt;STRONG&gt;Some changes with direct damage spells went live with the April 20th update&lt;/STRONG&gt;&lt;/FONT&gt;&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;Wizards are currently falling further and further behind in these areas, areas that they should actually excel given the major limitations on their damage potential. In reality, any class that isn't mana based should not even come close, and yet, many do, often exceeding the class by more than a minor amount. This is just exacerbated by the current trend of making fights last longer again, which actually only hurts classes that have built in limits on their damage, Wizards being the one that is probably the most affected by it. And this is without even taking into account mob abilities that affect casters to an even greater extent (high resists, mana drains, and even total immunities to spell damage).&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
